### Describe the Bug

I'm trying to use middleware to check a user's account for activity and redirect to the login page.



### Expected Behavior

I would expect the middleware to re-fetch pages with the previous 307 status

### To Reproduce

middleware.ts
```typescript
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from 'next/server';
import apiConstant from 'api/api-constants';

export async function middleware(req: NextRequest) {
  const token = req.cookies.get('token')?.value;
  const refresh_token = req.cookies.get('refresh_token')?.value;

  console.log(JSON.stringify({ token, refresh_token }));

  let login_url = `/login?redirect=${req.nextUrl.pathname}`;

  if (token && refresh_token) {
    const res = await fetch(apiConstant.me, {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ token, refresh_token }),
    });

    const { error, error_code, data } = await res.json();

    console.log(error, error_code, data);

    if (error) {
      if (error_code) login_url += `&error_code=${error_code}`;
    } else return NextResponse.next();
  }
  return NextResponse.redirect(new URL(login_url, req.url));
}

export const config = {
  matcher: [
    '/change-email',
    '/dashboard/:path*',
    '/license/:path*',
    '/modeling/order/:path*',
    '/notification',
    '/upload-model/:path*',
    '/user/:path*',
    '/verify',
    '/withdraw',
  ],
};

``` 


1. Active account
2. Lock account
3. When I open the dropdown, the links to the pages are declared in the matcher and they are preloaded with status 307
4. When I go to any page in section 4, I am redirected to the login page
5. When I log in successfully, I cannot go to the pages in section 4 (at this point the account has been unlocked)


https://github.com/vercel/next.js/assets/105255382/0b00fdc0-1fe8-4d0b-a91b-1b9f781f5599

